# Discord Bot Tokens Configuration
# 
# To set up your Discord bots:
# 1. Go to https://discord.com/developers/applications
# 2. Create a new application for each character (Peter, Brian, Stewie)
# 3. In each application, go to "Bot" section and create a bot
# 4. Copy the bot token and paste it below
# 5. Copy this file to .env in the root directory
#
# Make sure to invite each bot to your Discord server with the following permissions:
# - Send Messages
# - Read Message History
# - Use Slash Commands
# - Read Messages/View Channels

DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN_PETER=your_peter_bot_token_here
DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN_BRIAN=your_brian_bot_token_here
DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN_STEWIE=your_stewie_bot_token_here

# Optional: Override default service URLs if needed
# MESSAGE_ROUTER_URL=http://message-router:6005/orchestrate
# PETER_DISCORD_PORT=6011
# BRIAN_DISCORD_PORT=6012
# STEWIE_DISCORD_PORT=6013 